x \in \mathbb{N}
 \Gamma(x)=(x-1)!
\Gamma (x) = \int_0^\infty t^{x-1} \mathrm{e}^{-t}\,\mathrm{d}t
u=t^{x-1}\;\;,\;\;u'=(x-1)t^{x-2}\\v'=e^{-t}\;\;,\;\;v=-e^{-t}
\Gamma(x):=\int\limits_0^\infty t^{x-1}e^{-t}\,dt=\overbrace{\left.-(x-1)t^{x-2}e^{-t}\right|_0^\infty}^\text{This is zero}+(x-1)\int\limits_0^\infty t^{x-2}e^{-t}=
=:(x-1)\Gamma(x-1)
\,\Gamma(1)=1\,
